An Act amending title 33 Virgin Islands Code, chapter 4, section 72 relating to the highway
user tax
P ROPOSED BY: Senator Ray Fonseca
1 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the Virgin Islands:
2 SECTION 1. Title 33 Virgin Islands Code, chapter 4, section 72 is amended as follows:
3 (a) by inserting “)” after “Virgin Islands” where it appears in the second instance;
4 (b) by striking “of sixteen cents per pound” and inserting “based on weight
5 classification set forth below”; and
6 (c) by inserting after “$25.00” the following:
7 “Class 1: Weight 0000-6000 pounds – $0.16 per pound;
8 Class 2: Weight 6001-10,000 pounds – $0.18 per pound;
9 Class 3: Weight 10,001-14,000 pounds – $0.20 per pound;
10 Class 4: Weight 14,001-16,000 pounds – $0.22 per pound;
11 Class 5: Weight 16,001-19,500 pounds – $0.24 per pound;
12 Class 6: Weight 19,501-26,000 pounds – $0.26 per pound;
13 Class 7: Weight 26,001-33,000 pounds – Rate $0.28 per pound; and
14 Class 8: Weight 33,001 and up – $0.30 per pound.”

2
1 SECTION 2. This act take effect 60 days after enactment.
2 SECTION 3. The Virgin Islands Bureau of Internal Revenue shall make public
3 announcements from the enactment day of this act advising the public of the rate change.
4 BILL SUMMARY
5 This bill provides the for the payment of highway user tax based on the weight
6 classification of a vehicle.
